Commit Message: RangePicker 优化 * 日期面板： * 只选中开始日期，“确定”和“选择时间”灰置。 * 如未选择日期直接选择时间，开始日期和结束日期默认选中当天。 * 点击框外和确定均为确定操作。 * 时间面板： * 在时间页面，开始时间的默认状态为当前时间，结束时间的默认状态跟随开始时间。 * 开始时间的选择范围没有限制，结束时间的选择范围必须大于等于开始时间。 * 当开始时间选择了结束时间之后的时间（发生冲突），结束时间则自动切换到与开始时间相同的时间。

}
.rc-calendar-month-panel-year-select-arrow {
  display: none;
}
.rc-calendar-month-panel-next-year-btn {
  -webkit-user-select: none;
     -moz-user-select: none;
      -ms-user-select: none;
          user-select: none;
  right: 0;
}
.rc-calendar-month-panel-table {
  table-layout: fixed;
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: separate;
}
.rc-calendar-month-panel-cell {
  text-align: center;
}
.rc-calendar-month-panel-month {
  line-height: 78px;
  display: block;
  border-radius: 4px;
  border: 1px solid transparent;
}
.rc-calendar-month-panel-month:hover {
  background: #eeeeee;
}
.rc-calendar-month-panel-selected-cell .rc-calendar-month-panel-month {
  color: #ffffff;
  background-color: #3276b1;
  border-color: #285e8e;
}
.rc-calendar-year-panel {
  left: 0;
  top: 0;
  bottom: 0;
  right: 0;
  background: #ffffff;
  z-index: 10;
  position: absolute;
  outline: none;
}
.rc-calendar-year-panel-hidden {
  display: none;
}
.rc-calendar-year-panel-header {
  height: 30px;
  line-height: 30px;
  position: relative;
  text-align: center;
}
.rc-calendar-year-panel-header > a {
  font-weight: bold;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 4px 5px;
  text-align: center;
  width: 30px;
  height: 30px;
  line-height: 22px;
  border-radius: 4px;
}
.rc-calendar-year-panel-header > a:hover {
  background: #eeeeee;
}

Added content:
+[Streams](http://nodejs.org/api/stream.html "Stream") are node's best and most misunderstood idea<c> and EventStream is a toolkit to make creating and working with streams easy.<
>+Normally<c> streams are only used for IO<c> but in event stream we send all kinds of objects down the pipe. If your application's input and output are streams<c>  <
>+shouldn't the throughput be a stream too?  <
>+The *EventStream* functions resemble the array functions<c> because Streams are like Arrays<c> but laid out in time<c> rather than in memory.  <
>+All the `event-stream` functions return instances of `Stream`.<
>+`event-stream` creates [0.8 streams](https://github.com/joyent/node/blob/v0.8/doc/api/stream.markdown)<c> which are compatible with [0.10 streams](http://nodejs.org/api/stream.html "Stream").<
>

+## through (write?<c> end?)<
>+Reemits data synchronously. Easy way to create syncronous through streams.<
>+Pass in an optional `write` and `end` methods. They will be called in the <
>+context of the stream. Use `this.pause()` and `this.resume()` to manage flow.<
>+Check `this.paused` to see current flow state. (write always returns `!this.paused`)<
>+this function is the basis for most of the syncronous streams in `event-stream`.<
>+``` js<
>+es.through(function write(data) {<
>+    this.emit('data'<c> data)<
>+    //this.pause() <
>+  }<c><
>+  function end () { //optional<
>+    this.emit('end')<
>+  })<
>+```<
>+## mapSync (syncFunction)<
>+Same as `map`<c> but the callback is called synchronously. Based on `es.through`<
>+## split (matcher)<
>+Break up a stream and reassemble it so that each line is a chunk. matcher may be a `String`<c> or a `RegExp` <
>+Example<c> read every line in a file ...<
>+``` js<
>+  es.connect(<
>+    fs.createReadStream(file<c> {flags: 'r'})<c><
>+    es.split()<c><
>+    es.map(function (line<c> cb) {<
>+       //do something with the line <
>+       cb(null<c> line)<
>+    })<
>+  )<
>+```<
>+`split` takes the same arguments as `string.split` except it defaults to '
' instead of '<c>'<c> and the optional `limit` paremeter is ignored.<
>+[String#split](https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String/split)<
>+## join (seperator)<
>+create a through stream that emits `seperator` between each chunk<c> just like Array#join.<
>+(for legacy reasons<c> if you pass a callback instead of a string<c> join is a synonym for `es.wait`)<
>+## replace (from<c> to)<
>+Replace all occurences of `from` with `to`. `from` may be a `String` or a `RegExp`.  <
>+Works just like `string.split(from).join(to)`<c> but streaming.<

+##readable (asyncFunction) <
>+create a readable stream (that respects pause) from an async function.  <
>+while the stream is not paused<c>  <
>+the function will be polled with `(count<c> callback)`<c>  <
>+and `this`  will be the readable stream.<
>+``` js<
>+es.readable(function (count<c> callback) {<
>+  if(streamHasEnded)<
>+    return this.emit('end')<
>+  <
>+  //...<
>+  <
>+  this.emit('data'<c> data) //use this way to emit multiple chunks per call.<
>+      <
>+  callback() // you MUST always call the callback eventually.<
>+             // the function will not be called again until you do this.<
>+```<
>+you can also pass the data and the error to the callback.  <
>+you may only call the callback once.  <
>+calling the same callback more than once will have no effect.  <
>+All calls to write will return false (pause upstream)<c>  <
>+and end will not be sent downstream.  <
>+If the gate is open<c> let the stream through.  <

+//<
>+// readable (asyncFunction)<
>+// return a stream that calls an async function while the stream is not paused.<
>+//<
>+// the function must take: (count<c> callback) {...<
>+//<
>+es.readable = function (func<c> continueOnError) {<
>+  var stream = new Stream()<
>+    <c> i = 0<
>+    <c> paused = false<
>+    <c> ended = false<
>+  stream.readable = true  <
>+  stream.writable = false<
>+ <
>+  if('function' !== typeof func)<
>+    throw new Error('event-stream.readable expects async function')<
>+  <
>+  stream.on('end'<c> function () { ended = true })<
>+  <
>+  function get (err<c> data) {<
>+    if(err) {<
>+      stream.emit('error'<c> err)<
>+      if(!continueOnError) stream.emit('end')<
>+    } else if (arguments.length > 1)<
>+      stream.emit('data'<c> data)<
>+      <
>+    if(ended || paused) return<
>+    process.nextTick(function () {<
>+      try {<
>+        func.call(stream<c> i++<c> get)<
>+      } catch (err) {<
>+        stream.emit('error'<c> err)    <
>+      }<
>+    })<
>+  <
>+  }<
>+  stream.resume = function () {<
>+    paused = false<
>+    get()<
>+  }<
>+  process.nextTick(stream.resume)<
>+  stream.pause = function () {<
>+     paused = true<
>+  }<
>+  return stream<

>+EventEmitters in node are a brilliant idea that unfortunatly are under utilized by the node community. <

>+`map` does not guarantee mapped output order will be the same an written input.<
>+`map` will hold off on emitting `end` until all of it's map callbacks are complete.<
>+Each map MUST call the callback. it may callback with data<c> with an error or with no arguments<c> <
>+``` js<
>+  //callback mapped data<
>+  <

>+    <
>+  //drop this peice of data<

>+  <
>+  //if there was on error<
>+  <
>+  callback (error) //the event stream will emit 'error' instead of data for this step.<
>+```<
>+if a callback is not called map will think that it is still being worked on.<
>+If the callback is called more than once<c> every call but the first will be ignored.<

>+### reduce<
>+combine all incomingdata together into one item which will be emitted on recieving end.<
>+### pipe<
>+join multiple EventStreams together into one massive stream. <
>+the pipe will return an EventStream. Writing to the pipe will write to the first stream<c><
>+the pipe will emit data from the last stream.<

>+EventEmitters in node are a brilliant idea that are under utilized in the node community. <
>+they are at the heart of all the IO in node core<c> reading from files<c> or TCP<c> or the body <
>+of an http request or response is handled as a stream of events.<
>+A stream of events is a bit like an array<c> but an array layed out in time<c> rather than in memory.<
>+You can apply a map function to an array and create a new array<c> you could apply a similar <
>+map function to a stream of events to create a new stream. `map` functions<c> but also `fitler`<c> `reduce`<
>+and other functional programming idioms!<
>+event streams are great because they have a naturally scalable API. <
>+if the events in a stream can be stringified ane parsed then it will be relatively simple to split heavy <
>+parts of a stream into seperate processes<c> and to incorperate middlewares into the stream that might <
>+buffer or rate-limit or parallelize critical aspects of your event stream.<
>+Supporting this sort of programming is the purpose of this library.<

>+#!/usr/bin/env node<
>+/**<
>+ * Ported by Yosef on 24/08/2016.<

>+/**<
>+ POLYFILLS START<
>+ not required in nodejs<
>+ */<
>+var nginxBeautifier = require("./nginxbeautifier.js");<
>+//define nodejs modules<
>+var fs = require('fs');<
>+var path = require('path');<
>+var options = {<
>+    name: "nginxbeautifier"<c><
>+    spaces: 0<c><
>+    tabs: 0<c><
>+    dontJoinCurlyBracet: false<c><
>+    align: false<c><
>+    trailingBlankLines: false<c><
>+    recursive: false<c><
>+    inputPath: []<c><
>+    outputPath: []<c><

>+var knownArguments = {<
>+        "--help": function (input) {<
>+            if (input == "desc")<
>+                return "Show this help text.";<
>+            console.log("Usage: " + options.name + " [OPTION]... [FILE]...");<
>+            console.log("Description: Formats nginx conf files into a more readable format by re-indenting the lines.");<
>+            console.log("");<
>+            console.log("Mandatory arguments to long options are mandatory for short options too<c> Arguments are case insensitive.");<
>+            var argPrint = {};<
>+            for (var key in knownArguments) {<
>+                var desc = knownArguments[key]("desc");<
>+                if (argPrint[desc] == null)<
>+                    argPrint[desc] = '';<
>+                argPrint[desc] = key + "<c> " + argPrint[desc];<
>+            }<
>+            for (var desc in argPrint) {<
>+                console.log(argPrint[desc]<c> desc);<
>+            }<
>+            console.log("");<
>+            console.log("Usage examples:");<
>+            console.log("(1)>" + options.name + " -s 4 -r sites-enabled/");<
>+            console.log("(2)>" + options.name + " -s 4 -r /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/");<
>+            console.log("(3)>" + options.name + " -s 4 -i /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/site.conf -o /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/newSite.conf ");<
>+            console.log("(4)>" + options.name + " -s 4 -i /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/site.conf");<
>+            console.log("(5)>" + options.name + " -s 4 -i /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/*");<
>+            console.log("(6)>" + options.name + " -t 4 -i /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/*");<
>+            console.log("(7)>" + options.name + " -t 4 /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/*");<
>+            console.log("(8)>" + options.name + " -t 4 -i /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/* -o /etc/nginx/new-sites-enabled/*");<
>+            return false;<
>+        }<c><
>+        "--space": function (number) {<
>+            if (number == "desc")<
>+                return "Amount of spaces to indent with<c> Can not be used if tabs are specified."<
>+            else if (isNaN(number)) {<
>+                knownArguments["--space"](1);<
>+                return true;<
>+            }<
>+            if (options.tabs > 0) {<
>+                console.log("Error! tabs were already defined<c> please choose one or the other.")<
>+                knownArguments["--help"]();<
>+                process.exit();<
>+            }<
>+            options.spaces = parseInt(number);<
>+            nginxBeautifier.modifyOptions({INDENTATION: " ".repeat(options.spaces)});<
>+        }<c><
>+        "--tabs": function (number) {<
>+            if (number == "desc")<
>+                return "Amount of tabs to indent with<c> Can not be used if spaces are specified."<
>+            else if (isNaN(number)) {<
>+                knownArguments["--tabs"](1);<
>+                return true;<
>+            }<
>+            if (options.spaces > 0) {<

>+                process.exit();<
>+            }<
>+            options.tabs = parseInt(number);<
>+            nginxBeautifier.modifyOptions({INDENTATION: "	".repeat(options.tabs)});<
>+        }<c><
>+        "--blank-lines": function (input) {<
>+            if (input == "desc")<
>+                return "if set to true<c> an empty line will be inserted after opening brackets";<
>+            options.trailingBlankLines = true;<
>+        }<c><
>+        "--dont-join": function (input) {<
>+            if (input == "desc")<
>+                return "if set to true<c> commands such as 'server' and '{' will be on a seperate line<c> false by default ('server {' )";<

>+        }<
>+        <c><
>+        "--align": function (input) {<
>+            if (input == "desc")<
>+                return "if set to true<c> all applicable attribute values will be vertically aligned with each other";<
>+            options.align = true;<
>+        }<
>+        <c><
>+        "--recursive": function (input) {<
>+            if (input == "desc")<
>+                return "scan the whole current folder<c> and all sub folders recursively.";<
>+            options.recursive = true;<
>+            return false;<
>+        }<
>+        <c><
>+        "--input": function (file) {<
>+            var recursive = false;<
>+            if (file == "desc")<
>+                return "The file to input<c> is optional if you provide a path after all the arguments.";<
>+            if (file.startsWith("-"))<
>+                return true;<

>+                //knownArguments["--recursive"]();<
>+                recursive = true;<
>+                file = file.slice(0<c> file.length - 1);<
>+                file = file.length > 0 ? file : ".";<
>+            }<

>+        }<
>+        <c><
>+        "--output": function (file) {<
>+            var recursive = false;<
>+            if (file == "desc")<
>+                return "The file to output to<c> is optional if you provide a path after all the arguments.";<
>+            if (file.startsWith("-"))<
>+                return true;<

>+                // knownArguments["--recursive"]();<
>+                recursive = true;<
>+                file = file.slice(0<c> file.length - 1);<

>+            }<
>+            options.outputPath.push({name: file<c> recursive: recursive});<
>+        }<c><

>+            if (ext == "desc")<
>+                return "The extension of the config file to look for(.conf by default).";<
>+            if (ext.startsWith("-"))<
>+                return true;<
>+            options.extension = ext;<
>+        }<
>+    }<
>+;<
>+//shortcuts<
>+knownArguments["-h"] = knownArguments["--help"];<
